âœ… AI Chatbot Deployment â€“ Step by Step
Step 1: Prepare Project

Frontend â†’ React.js (UI)

Backend â†’ Python + FastAPI (AI + APIs)

LLM â†’ LLaMA 3.2 run via Ollama

RAG â†’ Retrieval-Augmented Generation for context-based answers

Database â†’ ChromaDB (Vector DB for embeddings)

ML packages â†’ PyPDF2, Sentence-Transformers, OpenCV

Goal: Full project local lo test chesi run cheyyadam.

Step 2: Containerization with Docker

Why? Environment-independent, scalable, consistent deployment

Actions:

Dockerfile create cheyadam

React frontend build copy

Python backend dependencies install

ML model setup

Docker Compose create cheyadam

Frontend container

Backend container

Database container (ChromaDB)

Command run:

docker-compose up -d


Containers run â†’ project environment ready

Step 3: Process Management â€“ PM2

Why? Continuous backend process run, auto-restart, zero downtime

Actions:

pm2 start python_backend.py --name "ai-backend"
pm2 save


Node.js backend (if any) kuda PM2 lo run cheyachu

Step 4: AWS EC2 Setup

EC2 instance create cheyadam

Security Group open ports:

22 â†’ SSH

80 â†’ HTTP

443 â†’ HTTPS

Docker install cheyadam

Container run cheyadam EC2 lo

Step 5: Domain & Subdomain â€“ GoDaddy

Main domain â†’ brihaspathi.com

Subdomain â†’ chatbot.brihaspathi.com

DNS Setup:

Subdomain A record â†’ EC2 public IP

TTL â†’ 600 sec

Step 6: Nginx Reverse Proxy

Why? Incoming traffic handle, backend secure access, HTTPS

Configuration Example:

server {
    listen 80;
    server_name chatbot.brihaspathi.com;

    location / {
        proxy_pass http://localhost:3000;  # React frontend
    }

    location /api/ {
        proxy_pass http://localhost:5000; # FastAPI backend
    }
}

Step 7: SSL / HTTPS

Letâ€™s Encrypt / Certbot install

Command:

sudo certbot --nginx -d chatbot.brihaspathi.com


Why? Secure communication, professional deployment

Step 8: Connect Backend & Frontend

React frontend â†’ FastAPI backend APIs call

FastAPI backend â†’ Ollama â†’ LLaMA 3.2 runs model

RAG â†’ Search embeddings in ChromaDB

Response â†’ Frontend display to user

Step 9: Testing & Monitoring

Access: https://chatbot.brihaspathi.com

Test:

Login / authentication

Question â†’ Answer flow

RAG + LLM correctness

PM2 + Docker logs â†’ monitor containers

Nginx logs â†’ monitor web traffic

Step 10: Production Ready

Fully containerized â†’ portable across environments

Continuous backend â†’ PM2

Secure â†’ Nginx + SSL

Domain integrated â†’ users can access chatbot

